name: ethyl 4-cyanophenylacetate
Reason: 4-Cyanophenyl can increase the melting point due to the additional pi-pi interactions and rigidity, estimated at around +20 to +30°C. The cyano group introduces a strong withdrawing group, raising the melting point by approximately +50°C. The methyl group reduces the melting point by approximately -10°C due to the reduced molecular weight and volume.
